## **Install NoMachine on NVIDIA Jetson (ARM64)**
This guide shows how to download and install NoMachine on an NVIDIA Jetson device and configure a dummy display so NoMachine works without a physical monitor.
Prerequisites
NVIDIA Jetson device (ARM64)
Ubuntu-based Jetpack
Internet connection


# Download the ARM64 .deb package
wget https://download.nomachine.com/download/9.3/Arm/nomachine_9.3.7_1_arm64.deb

Install the Package

sudo dpkg -i nomachine_9.3.7_1_arm64.deb

Install Dummy Display

Create a tsxt file name sudo nano /etc/X11/xorg.conf and save
Section "Device"
    Identifier "Configured Video Device"
    Driver "dummy"
EndSection

Section "Monitor"
    Identifier "Configured Monitor"
    HorizSync 31.5-48.5
    VertRefresh 50-70
EndSection

Section "Screen"
    Identifier "Default Screen"
    Monitor "Configured Monitor"
    Device "Configured Video Device"
    DefaultDepth 24
    SubSection "Display"
        Depth 24
        Modes "1280x720"
    EndSubSection
EndSection

then Reboot
sudo reboot
